gomodel:SYNGO_2318  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Fig. 3 Legend:\n-Literal \"Double-immunofluorescence staining for cad11 and synaptophysin or GluR1 in cultured hippocampal neurons. (A) Double-staining for cad11 (green) and synaptophysin (red). (B) Double-staining for cad11 (green) and GluR1 (red). Insets show enlargement of the portions enclosed\nwith rectangles. mAb 2F9D9 was used for the cad11 staining. Arrowheads point to examples of sites in which the two color signals overlapped.\"\n\nDiscussion:\n-Literal: \"This study demonstrated that cad11 proteins were densely distributed in synaptic zones of the hippocampus, and their distribution overlapped with that of synaptophysin and GluR1 in cultured hippocampal neurons, suggesting that they were associated with at least a certain population of synapse.\". Experimental description: M&Ms Section: \"Immunocytochemistry for Cultured Hippocampal Neurons\"\n-Literal: \"Briefly, hippocampi were dissected from E17 mouse embryos and dissociated ...\"" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-6893-6177" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-5265-6306" ;
        dc:date           "2018-01-15" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_2318" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .
